Here is a clean, production-ready implementation of **Deep clone an object (variant 14)** in Javascript.

### Explanation
Creates a deep copy of an object, handling nested objects, arrays, and primitive types. Specifically, this handles variant case 14.

### Implementation
```javascript
function deepClone_v14(obj) {
  if (obj === null || typeof obj !== 'object') return obj;
  if (Array.isArray(obj)) return obj.map(deepClone_v14);
  const cloned = {};
  for (let key in obj) {
    if (obj.hasOwnProperty(key)) {
      cloned[key] = deepClone_v14(obj[key]);
    }
  }
  return cloned;
}
```

